
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 29/120 – Pivot

🎤 Interview Question

You are given a sales DataFrame with the following columns:

employee, department, sales

Write PySpark code to:

1. Pivot the department column.


2. Display the total sales of each employee under separate department columns.




---

📊 Input Dataset

employee	department	sales

John	IT	1000
John	HR	500
Alice	IT	2000
Bob	Finance	1500
Alice	HR	800



---

✅ Expected Output

employee	Finance	HR	IT

John	NULL	500	1000
Alice	NULL	800	2000
Bob	1500	NULL	NULL



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import sum

df.groupBy("employee") \
  .pivot("department") \
  .agg(sum("sales")) \
  .show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is Pivot?

Answer

Pivot converts row values into column names.


---

Q2. Which SQL operation is equivalent to Pivot?

Answer

It is conceptually similar to a PIVOT operation in SQL.


---

Q3. When is Pivot commonly used?

Answer

Sales reports

Monthly reports

Dashboard generation

Cross-tab reporting



