⭐⭐⭐⭐☆ Question 30/120 – Rollup

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to calculate:

1. Total salary by department.


2. Grand total salary of all departments.




---

📊 Input Dataset

department	salary

IT	60000
IT	70000
HR	45000
HR	48000
Finance	55000



---

✅ Expected Output

department	total_salary

IT	130000
HR	93000
Finance	55000
NULL	278000


> The NULL row represents the grand total.




---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import sum

df.rollup("department") \
  .agg(sum("salary").alias("total_salary")) \
  .show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is Rollup?

Answer

rollup() generates hierarchical subtotals along with the grand total.


---

Q2. What does the NULL row represent?

Answer

The NULL row represents the overall total across all groups.


---

Q3. Where is Rollup used?

Answer

Financial reports

Sales summaries

BI dashboards

Executive reporting



