⭐⭐⭐⭐☆ Question 31/120 – Cube

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to calculate salary totals for every combination of:

Department

City


including all subtotals and the grand total.


---

📊 Input Dataset

department	city	salary

IT	Mumbai	60000
IT	Pune	70000
HR	Delhi	45000
Finance	Hyderabad	55000



---

✅ Expected Output (Sample)

department	city	total_salary

IT	Mumbai	60000
IT	Pune	70000
IT	NULL	130000
HR	Delhi	45000
HR	NULL	45000
Finance	Hyderabad	55000
Finance	NULL	55000
NULL	Mumbai	60000
NULL	Pune	70000
NULL	Delhi	45000
NULL	Hyderabad	55000
NULL	NULL	230000



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import sum

df.cube(
    "department",
    "city"
).agg(
    sum("salary").alias("total_salary")
).show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Difference between Rollup and Cube?

Answer

rollup() generates hierarchical subtotals.

cube() generates all possible combinations of grouping columns.



---

Q2. Which one produces more rows?

Answer

cube() generally produces more rows because it computes every grouping combination.


---

Q3. Which is more expensive?

Answer

cube() is more computationally expensive than rollup() due to the larger number of aggregations.


